One of 779 shortest trees showing ancestral areas for five clades, B = central US and Canada, D = southwestern US and Mexico, E = Central America, F = western South America. Red = species originally placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B41DCFFBFFFF1FDC1FAE08B6FFA8D" authority=", Blue" authorityName="Blue" box="[583,773,1312,1336]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Holomelina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93FE64DFFBFFFF1FDC1FAE08AAFFA8D" box="[583,709,1313,1336]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Holomelina</emphasis>
